  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Using local analgesia in laparoscopic surgery in order to reduce pain and to reduce the use
      of narcotic drugs.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      At the end of laparoscopic surgery the investigators will spray ropivacaine in the surgical
      site; and later the investigators will monitor pain intensity and use of analgesic drugs
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
